  "dateModified": "2026-04-27",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-27",
  "description": "Cybernetic postliberalism positioned relative to adjacent postliberal critiques: right-postliberalism (Deneen, Vermeule), left-postliberalism (Brown, Streeck), affect-theoretical critique (Berlant, Hochschild), Foucauldian governmentality, settler-colonial studies, accelerationism, Frankfurt-school inheritance. The school's specific contributions are the cybernetic-systems framing, the closure claim, the energetic-substrate presupposition, and the recurrence with the church-pastoral.",
  "name": "Cybernetic Postliberalism in Context",
